54 Taxi-extrodinare.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uhippolytahelios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyta Helios</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/5/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:22:54 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">sheesh!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I don't see why everyone is panicking.  I mean, rogues are the masters of invisibility and they still do the most damage of any melee class.  I just interpreted it as pointing out that the newer wizard teleportation abilities wouldn't be infringed on--but every caster has direct damage spells, so they're technically all on our &quot;turf.&quot;  It doesn't mean we can't be the best at direct damage, just that the &quot;unique&quot; abilities are teleport-related.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulenadaynastardew.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenadayna Stardew</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/5/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:46:46 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=c:\windows\desktop\lena.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: WTF!!!!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">It doesn't mean we can't be the best at direct damage, just that the &quot;unique&quot; abilities are teleport-related. <br>
<br>
  Lyta, that's exactly what wizards *don't* want.  Teleports are viewed as our group friendly ability for whatever reason, and it's this thinking that needs to change.  Teleports are grouply friendly for about a minute, then the person you're teleporting disbands and goes on his or her way.<br>
</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uhippolytahelios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyta Helios</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/5/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>6:40:28 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">but</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The main thing we bring to a group is direct damage, in huge quantities--but that is not a &quot;unique&quot; thing, because all casters have some form of DD or another.  We should be obviously better than anyone else in direct damage, and we've all had all sorts of ideas about how we could have direct damage that is more obviously better than other classes--bigger blasts, more efficient blasts, faster blasts, better mana regen, less resisted blasts, etc. etc. etc.--but those ideas are all just forms of direct damage, which isn't a unique ability.  Every nuke we have could be doubled in damage, halved in cost, and punch through resistances three times as well, and it would still not be &quot;unique&quot;.  The new types of teleports, however, are the unique bits--in the literal sense of things no one else has.<br>
<br>
I still think people are seriously overreacting to nothing in particular.<br>
<br>
